When a decoding error occurs, the whole byte array to be deserialized is printed to the standard output. This can be quite disruptive, especially when dealing with large serialized objects. Truncate the undecodable array to its first 500 characters when printing it out.
Add support for deserializing unmodifiable collections. Fix #114
fix issue where an array didn't get registered at correct handle until AFTER it was fully read, which broke some cases of self-referential structures.

Collections.unmodifiableMap(LinkedHashMap) serialization does not preserve ordering

Motivation:

Order should be preserved when serializing an ordered unmodifiable map / set.

Modifications:

Use LinkedHashMap and LinkedHashSet as the internal map / set.

Result:

Order is preserved when serializing an ordered unmodifiable map / set.

Unmodifiable serializers for JSON config only

Motivation:

Move unmodifiable serializers to JSON configs as they are not required for default configuration

Modifications:

Moved serializer configuration to constructJsonConf and replaced linked map / set with normal.

Result:

Correct behaviour.
If we replace the object still always return the type we serialized

Fix #195: Added FSTLogger shim to delegate to logging frameworks

This allows FST to log to other logging frameworks (or none at
all).
This change does not include any implementations, it may make
sense to add a stdout/stderr binding in test sources.

When InputStream reads fail, propagate the exception

FSTInputStream.readNextChunk throws on failure rather than
silently assuming the stream has completed.

In situations where it's necessary to power through failing
streams, a wrapped stream can be provided which reads until an
exception is thrown, then reports that it is finished.
More memory leakage with callbacks fixed

Avoid re-reading data from a cached buffer

readObject returning the last object the FSTObjectInput read.

Fix getCLInfo thread safety where null class prematurely unlocks

In this scenario, the finally block can unlock rwLock that has
already been acquired by another invocation.

Making Int2ObjectMap configurable through a factory.
This change allows to register a new Int2ObjectMap factory to the configuration
while keeping the older implementation as the default.
To set up a new factory clients of the library will have to create
a factory and set it through the configuration.
In addition clearing of the default configuration is now responsible for
deciding how to clean itself while maintining implementation details encapsulated.
